Command line:
pwd - getting your current directory.
ls - listing all the file in the folder.
cd - change directory.


Files Purposes:
noed-modules - all the npm packages.
src - contains code for the website js/css/html.
assets folder - This is where you store the image you want to display.
public folder - contains file taht should be available to the public. It means we can access these using URL.
eslint = hightlights problems in js code. (Need to install eslint extension to works).
Vite - tool that we used to set up this project. Also helps us build the website. Also creates a server(A server puts our website at a URL).

